Property.description: SCHEDULE A SHOWING ONLINE AT: showmojo.com/lrt/cb03db502b ---- **BEAUTIFUL FURNISHED STUDIO WITH SHARED KITCHEN** **All utilities included for + $100!** 1010 Bush St. is a secure and communal residency apartment building. Each unit has its own sink, providing residents with convenience and privacy. The fully equipped community kitchen with two ranges, two microwaves, and two large sinks, as well as free lockers for cutlery and cookware, make it easy for residents to prepare and store their meals. The recently redesigned lounge features a flat-screen TV, WiFi, and comfortable seating provides a space for residents to relax and socialize with their neighbors. Overall, 1010 Bush St. is a great option for those looking for affordable and communal living in a safe and convenient location. This unit is fully furnished with a bed, desk, chair, tv, mini fridge, microwave. It has a private bathroom as well. All utilities will be included for +$100. NEIGHBORHOOD: 1010 Bush St. is located in Lower Nob Hill, a vibrant and diverse neighborhood in San Francisco. The area offers a unique blend of relaxed and trendy vibes, with plenty of attractions for residents to explore. Its central location adjacent to Union Square, Chinatown, Downtown SF, and FiDi makes it a convenient and accessible spot for those looking to explore the city. The Grand Penthouse of 181 Fremont features nearly 7000 square feet of extraordinary water views including all four iconic Bay Area Bridges, stretching from the Golden Gate and the Pacific Ocean to the Marin Headlands, East Bay Hills and the South Bay. These unmatched vistas infuse sunlight across all of the home's four bedrooms, six and a half baths, grand salon, family room and a spectacular study which overlooks the Transamerica Pyramid and Alcatraz. The abundant natural light extends to the spacious dining room, primary bedroom with north and west views, dual primary baths and a spectacular exhibition-style kitchen with custom Rossana cabinets and counter seating. The thoughtful, elegant design of this one-of-a-kind residence is credited to Mass Beverly and Elevate Interiors.

Sometimes beauty is subjective - other times, it's undeniable. 1919 Mariposa is certainly the latter. Reimagined in 2016, this striking home blends bold modern architecture with warm, Scandinavian-inspired design. The top floor is a showstopper: an open-concept great room with walk-out decks front and back, sweeping city views, and space for large-scale dining and lounging. The chef's kitchen features floor-to-ceiling wood cabinetry, quartz counters, high-end appliances, a picture window framing city views, and direct access to a front deck which leads to the expansive roof deck with panoramic city and bay views. The middle floor includes four bedrooms and 2.5 baths. The serene primary suite features a walk-in closet, garden access, and a luxe ensuite bath with steam shower and double sinks. Three more spacious bedrooms and two stylish baths complete the level. The entry floor offers a flexible media/guest room, full bath, laundry room, an infrared sauna and access to the spacious 2-car garage. Outdoor highlights include two main-level decks, a lush garden with mature palms, and a sun-drenched roof deck, perfect for Potrero Hill's microclimate. Just steps from Whole Foods, Jackson Park, La Contessa, Louie's etc. Easy access to freeways. Sometimes beauty is not up for debate.

Urban loft living meets city convenience in this 1BD/2BA live/work loft in Potrero Hill, just steps from the Dogpatch. Soaring 14+ ft ceilings and expansive west-facing windows fill the space with natural light, while polished concrete floors and exposed wood beams add industrial flair. The open main level features a modern kitchen with quartz counters, European cabinets, a suite of stainless steel Miele appliances: gas cooktop, electric convection oven, dishwasher and microwave, and a Liebherr refrigerator. It also boasts lighted, soft close drawers. In-unit laundry, an expansive living area and a full bath complete this floor. Up the spiral staircase, the enormous primary suite includes an en-suite bath, and organized closet. On hot days the ceiling fan, combined with operable windows on both sides of the home will cool you right down. With only one shared wall, enjoy privacy and quiet in this boutique building. Extras include a mapped garage parking space with room for storage at the front of it, and a shared patio just across the hall from your front door with plentiful seating and a barbecue. Close to Caltrain (electrified and much quieter!), I-280, parks, shops and restaurants galore, this loft offers the ultimate blend of function, style, and location. Walk Score of 94.

Experience the exceptional privilege of 1/10th fractional ownership at Fairmont Heritage Place Ghirardelli Square, where the comfort of home meets the luxury of urban living, San Francisco-style. Starting at your arrival, with valet service available to park your car in the owner parking garage. This stunning 2-bedroom, 2.5 bathroom fully furnished unit features a fully equipped kitchen, which can be stocked with your favorite items by the Owner Services team, a living room with fireplace, and amazing bay views from the bay windows. Unwind in spa-like bathroom and enjoy the convenience of an in-room washer and dryer. Enjoy weekly Wine and Cheese Hour in the Owner's Lounge, relax outdoors on numerous terraces with fire pits, and get to know fellow owners at special Owner Social Events. This is a 1/10th floating fractional interest which entitles the owner the right to use any 2 BR unit, subject to availability. Ownership at Fairmont Heritage Place Ghirardelli Square offers 5 weeks (35 nights) of occupancy yearly. You may use the 5 weeks at Ghirardelli Square or use some of your time traveling around the globe to other Fairmont, Raffles and Accor properties worldwide. Fractional ownership includes the elite Accor Diamond Membership and exchange privileges with the Registry Collection.
